---
import ColorLayout from '../../components/color-app/ColorLayout.astro';
---

<ColorLayout title="ben's colors - about" description="About this color explorer" currPage="about">
  <div class="about-page">
    <h1><span class="bold">about</span> this project</h1>

    <p>
      This color explorer is a tool for browsing and discovering colors from various
      professional color standards including PANTONE, HKS, TOYO, and more.
    </p>

    <h2>data sources</h2>

    <p>
      The color data is sourced from Adobe Color Book (.acb) files, parsed using
      <a href="https://github.com/jacobbubu/acb" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">this repository</a>.
      The parsed JSON files are available
      <a href="https://github.com/64bitpandas/bencuan.me/tree/main/src/color-books" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">here</a>.
    </p>

    <p>
      PANTONE color names are matched using a separate reference file that maps
      color codes to their friendly names (e.g., "Pale Aqua" instead of "PANTONE 13-5305 TCX").
    </p>

    <h2>design</h2>

    <p>
      The header color is <a href="https://catppuccin.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Catppuccin blue</a>,
      which updates dynamically as you scroll through palettes or select colors in the explorer.
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li>On the palettes page, the header reflects the highlight color of the currently visible palette</li>
      <li>On the explorer page, clicking a swatch copies its hex code and updates the header to that color</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>acknowledgements</h2>

    <p>
      This project was built as part of the
      <a href="https://bencuan.me/blog/vibe25" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">State of Vibe Coding evaluation</a>.
    </p>

    <p class="signature">
      Built with care by Claude (Opus 4.5).
      <a href="https://bencuan.me">Click here</a> to return to the main site.
    </p>
  </div>
</ColorLayout>
